Blackjack Game (Python)

A simple command-line Blackjack game built with Python.
The player competes against the computer following standard Blackjack rules, with an interactive CLI experience and ASCII art logo.

Features

Classic Blackjack gameplay (player vs computer)

Automatic card dealing and score calculation

Handles Ace (11 or 1) adjustment to prevent busting

Blackjack detection (21 with two cards)

Computer follows standard rule (hits until score â‰¥ 17)

Clear win/lose/draw result messages

Replayable game loop without restarting the program

Clean, function-based and beginner-friendly code structure

ASCII art logo displayed at the start of each game

How It Works

Run the program

The Blackjack logo is displayed

Both the player and the computer are dealt two cards

The player can:

Type y to draw another card (hit)

Type n to stop drawing cards (stand)

The game ends immediately if:

The player gets Blackjack

The computer gets Blackjack

The player goes over 21

After the player stands:

The computer draws cards until its score reaches at least 17

Final hands and scores are displayed

The result is shown (win / lose / draw)

The player can choose to play again or exit
